post_text:
Attention Panther Fans

Pikeville High School is excited to partner with two of our local businesses, Bit Source & Mountain Top Media, to provide fans from all over the country livestream access to our home sporting events and other school events throughout the school year.

Fans will be able to access a subscription-based live video feed at mountain-topsports.com starting with our football team’s home game vs. Belfry next Friday night on September 18th at 7:30.

This partnership also helps to financially ensure all of our Pikeville athletic programs are run at an elite level.

With limited seating during these unprecedented times at our home sporting events, this also allows local fans the opportunity to watch our games that otherwise would not be able to view them.

GO PANTHERS!!!

Pikeville Independent Schools is sharing a COVID-19 Update with Kristy Ward Orem.
August 21 at 12:16 PM ·

Starting Wednesday Aug 26th we transition from the USDA Summer Feeding Program back to National School Lunch & Breakfast! What does that mean for you?
1. PES Students PK-6th are all Free Breakfast & Lunch Daily this year. So you have 1 Form to fill out. To recieve meals Aug 26th and after via delivery, we must have permission to deliver meals for each student via this form: http://bit.ly/PISDLunch2020
2. A. PHS Parents of students 7th-12th will still be required to fill out the USDA Meal Benefits Form found in the Parent Infinite Campus Portal same as last year. Instructions to find that form in IC Portal are linked here: http://bit.ly/mealbenefitform2020
B. To recieve meals Aug 26th and after via delivery, we must have permission to deliver meals for each student via this form: http://bit.ly/PISDLunch2020

Pikeville Independent announces partnership with Edgenuity to serve as the district’s digital learning platform for its K-12 Online Academy.

Edgenuity is a leading provider for on-line learning solutions and was recently named the EdTech Digest, Digital Courseware Solution 2020 Winner. Since the companies conception in 1998 they have served over four million students bringing a wealth of experience to the table. AdvancedEd accredited and NCAA approved among many others.

We are in the final stages of piecing together the best products Edgenuity has to offer to better serve our students and families who will choose the Online Academy this coming Fall. Families may choose the Online Academy option on the 2020 Back to School Intent Form which is due August 5th: http://bit.ly/PISD2020Intent

Edgenuity

post_text: Good afternoon! Please join us live on Wednesday afternoon beginning at 1pm. We will discuss our plans for reopening our schools, as well as the calendar for the 2020-2021 school year. Our team continues to work extremely hard to assure our students receive the very best education in an environment that will help to keep both our students and team members safe and healthy. Thank you for your patience and support during this time, and for the feedback that you have provided. We will be revamping the student survey and releasing it following the information presented on Wednesday. This will allow that survey to be more meaningful and relevant as we continue to grow our plan. We are grateful for our many community partners, the wonderful members of our team here at Pikeville, and for our families who are so engaged in the educational process. We look forward to sharing with you on Wednesday. We hope you enjoy your weekend!

shared_text:
Pikeville Bands
March 12 at 8:27 PM ·

The Pikeville Wind Band gave an exciting and emotional performance at yesterday's KMEA band assessment. The students received unanimous distinguished ratings from all judges in both the performance and sight-reading categories.

The Pikeville Concert Band performed with excellence receiving unanimous distinguished ratings from all three judges. The band received a proficient rating in sight-reading, which requires the students to perform a piece of music that they have never rehearsed.

Following assessment, the Pikeville Varsity Band traveled to Rupp Arena to support the Lady Panthers in the KHSAA Sweet Sixteen Basketball Tournament.

Pikeville Bands expresses our sincere gratitude to our student-teacher, Hunter Plymale, who has been a tremendous help to us this semester. His contributions and teaching have helped us reach many musical goals. We wish him all the best in his future endeavors.

text:
Congratulations Dr. Bersaglia and Pikeville Bands! Panther Proud 🐾

Pikeville Bands
March 12 at 8:27 PM ·

The Pikeville Wind Band gave an exciting and emotional performance at yesterday's KMEA band assessment. The students received unanimous distinguished ratings from all judges in both the performance and sight-reading categories.

The Pikeville Concert Band performed with excellence receiving unanimous distinguished ratings from all three judges. The band received a proficient rating in sight-reading, which requires the students to perform a piece of music that they have never rehearsed.

Following assessment, the Pikeville Varsity Band traveled to Rupp Arena to support the Lady Panthers in the KHSAA Sweet Sixteen Basketball Tournament.

Pikeville Bands expresses our sincere gratitude to our student-teacher, Hunter Plymale, who has been a tremendous help to us this semester. His contributions and teaching have helped us reach many musical goals. We wish him all the best in his future endeavors.
